items.content_html:
Summary

All these features have following warning on mdn/content pages:

Warning: This interface is deprecated and is no more on the standard track. Do not use it anymore. Use the File and Directory Entries API instead.

For example https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/DirectoryEntrySync#sect2

Supporting details

  • https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=695508#c22
  • mdn/content#15815
items.title: Mark file system sync APIs 'deprecated'

items.content_html:
Summary

Firefox 103 add support for CSS trig functions behind layout.css.trig.enabled flag.

Test results and supporting details

Source: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1774589#c1

To make sure, I tested cos() function in codepen using Firefox 103.0.2 (64-bit), with the flag enabled.
items.title: Firefox support for CSS trig functions: `sin()`, `cos()`, `tan()`

items.content_html:
Summary

As per the guidelines these features are experimental.

If a feature is supported behind incompatible prefixes only (such as -webkit- in one engine and -moz- in another), no matter how many engines support the feature overall, then set experimental to true. If two or more engines support a feature behind a common prefix (such as -webkit- only), then set experimental to false.
items.title: Mark features supported behind incompatible prefix 'experimental'

items.content_html:
Summary

As per the guidelines these features are experimental.

If a feature is supported behind flags only, no matter how many engines, then set experimental to true.
items.title: Mark features supported behind only flags 'experimental'
